      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">7.102</ph> Policy.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d401e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d408e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                   Agencies shall perform acquisition
planning and conduct market research (see <xref href="FAR-i1114815.dita#i1114815"
                        base="i1114815"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  10</xref>) for all acquisitions
in order to promote and provide for-</p>
               <ol id="d401e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d408e30" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                         Acquisition
of commercial items or, to the extent that commercial items suitable
to meet the agency’s needs are not available, nondevelopmental items,
to the maximum extent practicable <ph class="- topic/ph ">(<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                 format="html"
                                 scope="external"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2377</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                 format="html"
                                 scope="external"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3307</xref>);</ph> and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d408e48" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                         Full and
open competition (see <xref href="FAR-i1120119.dita#i1120119"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>)
or, when full and open competition is not required in accordance
with <ph class="- topic/ph ">
                           <xref href="FAR-i1120119.dita#i1120119"
                                 base="i1120119"
                                 outputclass="fm:Part"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>,</ph> to obtain
competition to the maximum extent practicable, with due regard to
the nature of the supplies or services to be acquired (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2305(a)(1)(A)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3306a)(1)</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d408e72" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                         Selection
of appropriate contract type in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1105247.dita#i1105247"
                              base="i1105247"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  16</xref>; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d408e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                         Appropriate
consideration of the use of pre-existing contracts, including interagency
and intra-agency contracts, to fulfill the requirement, before awarding
new contracts. (See <xref href="FAR-i8_002.dita#i8_002"
                              base="i1118176"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.002</xref> through <xref href="FAR-i1118226.dita#i1118226"
                              base="i1118226"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.004</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1102787.dita#i1102787"
                              base="i1102787"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  17.5</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d408e104" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                   This planning
shall integrate the efforts of all personnel responsible for significant
aspects of the acquisition. The purpose of this planning is to ensure
that the Government meets its needs in the most effective, economical,
and timely manner. Agencies that have a detailed acquisition planning
system in place that generally meets the requirements of <xref href="FAR-i1118917.dita#i1118917"
                        base="i1118917"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">7.104</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1118935.dita#i1118935"
                        base="i1118935"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">7.105</xref> need not revise
their system to specifically meet all of these requirements.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
